## Push Summary — skrptiq-cli (main)

### What shipped
Visible mode switching for the CLI — three modes with distinct visual identity:

**Command mode** (default) — `❯` prompt, profile name left, exit hint right. Slash commands work, bare text prompts to enter chat mode.

**Chat mode** (`/chat`) — `💬` prompt, "chat" left context, provider name + "/exit to return" right. All bare text goes to the LLM handler (placeholder until wired). Detects default provider from settings.

**Run mode** (`/run <workflow>`) — `▶` prompt (green), "run" left context, workflow name + "/exit or esc to cancel" right. Bare text goes to gate/approval handler (placeholder until wired).

**Mode transitions:**
- `/chat` → enters chat mode
- `/run <name>` → enters run mode
- `/exit` → returns to command mode from any mode
- `esc` → exits current mode (or cancels overlay)
- Mode label, prompt symbol, and context line all update visually

